snippet.textDisplay:
Theory on the ending: Madison shows up last minute at the rose ceremony. Peter sends Victoria home. Madison reluctantly accepts the rose but soon realizes she really can’t go through with it (feeling like her trust has been broken). She goes home right before the final rose ceremony.

Hanna Anne finds out and is super upset. She feels she’s been so strong throughout the process and has unconditionally supported Peter - but now has been put in a terrible situation of not knowing whether she was going to be Peter’s first choice. Suspecting it was going to be Madison and realizing that Peter now has no choice but to pick her is too much to bear. Rather than put herself through this, she also decides to leave. This maybe the twist that no one has been expecting.

In the end, Peter is alone. He flies back to see his family for support. He’s confused but his mom tells him to get it together and “bring her home to us!” This could be her just talking in general about his future wife OR she’s specifically talking about Madison. He realizes that he can’t give up and will have to fight to get her back.

He goes to see her profusely apologizing for screwing up. He tells her how much he loves / cares for her and knew it all along but was just stupid. She loves him back but she just can’t do it given their different values or she says she needs time to think. I this is where AFTR may begin - with Madison having had time to think and reflect on their relationship / future together. She will tell him yay or nay - and in general, we’ll find out whether they’re together or not (very likely because he looks exhausted and not so happy)!

What do ya’ll think!? Possible?
